ciscoCryptoAcceleratorMIB.name: ciscoCryptoAcceleratorMIB
ciscoCryptoAcceleratorMIB.contactinfo: Cisco Systems Customer Service Postal: 170 W Tasman Drive San Jose, CA 95134 USA Tel: +1 800 553-NETS E-mail: cs-ipsecurity@cisco.com
ciscoCryptoAcceleratorMIB.description: The MIB module for monitoring the identity, status, activity and faults of crypto accelerator (CA) modules used in devices implementing security services. The purpose of this MIB is to facilitate the following: 1) facilitate the discovery of hardware crypto accelerator modules installed in a security device 2) monitor the activity, faults and performance of hardware crypto accelerators and help the Network Management Station (NMS) correlate the performance of the CA modules with that of the security services (IPsec, SSL, SSH, PKI etc) using the modules.

CAModuleType.name: CAModuleType
CAModuleType.description: This type yields the marketing label of the module type and supplements the corresponding entPhysicalVendorType MIB variable, if the crypto accelerator has an entry in entPhysicalTable. The value 'other' has been provided to keep the MIB still applicable while new crypto accelerators emerge. 'software' denotes the software implementation of crypto functions. 'integrated' denotes crypto accelerator modules which are integrated into the managed entity and are hence not modular. 'sep' and 'sepe' are scalable encryption processors used in VPN3000 series concentrators. 'a1700VpnModule' identifies the crypto accelerator used in in 1700 series routers. 'aimVpn' series of crypto accelerators are designed specifically for 2600 and 3700 platforms. Further, the aimVpnII series also function on 2800 series routers. 'aimVpn' series of crypto accelerators are designed specifically for 2600 and 2700 platforms. 'isa' is designed for 7200 series routers. 'vam' series of crypto accelerators are to be used on 7200 and 7300 series routers. 'vpnsm' denotes the Catalyst 6500 VPN service module, which is deemed a sophisticated 'crypto accelerator'. The 'caviumNitrox' series of crypto accelerators represent the crypto accelerator chipsets used in ASA devices.

CAModuleCount.name: CAModuleCount
CAModuleCount.description: This type denotes the count of crypto accelerators.

CAProtocolType.name: CAProtocolType
CAProtocolType.description: The security protocol using the services of the crypto accelerator module. The list of protocols supported commonly by crypto accelerators include Internet Key Exchange (ike), IP Security Phase-2 protocols (ipsec), Secure Shell (ssh), Secure Socket Layer (ssl) and Secure Real-time Transport Protocol (srtp). The value 'other' has been provided so that the MIB may still be valid while new protocols emerge and the MIB has not been updated to enumerate them.

ccaSupportsHwCrypto.name: ccaSupportsHwCrypto
ccaSupportsHwCrypto.description: This MIB object assumes the value of True if the managed device is capable of including hardware crypto accelerator.

ccaSupportsModularHwCrypto.name: ccaSupportsModularHwCrypto
ccaSupportsModularHwCrypto.description: This MIB object assumes the value of True if the managed device supports field removable hardware crypto accelerators.

ccaMaxAccelerators.name: ccaMaxAccelerators
ccaMaxAccelerators.description: The maximum number of hardware crypto accelerators which may be simultaneously operational in this device. If the managed device can support only software encryption, the value of this MIB object should be set to zero. If there is not set limit on the maximum number of crypto accelerator modules which the managed device can support, the agent should return a value of '-1' for this MIB variable.

ccaMaxCryptoThroughput.name: ccaMaxCryptoThroughput
ccaMaxCryptoThroughput.description: The maximum crypto throughput that may be supported by the managed device with the current number of active crypto accelerators. If this value cannot be determined, the agent should return a value of 0.

ccaMaxCryptoConnections.name: ccaMaxCryptoConnections
ccaMaxCryptoConnections.description: The maximum number of VPN flows (connections) the managed device can support with the current number of active crypto accelerators. If this value cannot be determined, the agent should return a value of 0.

ccaGlobalNumActiveAccelerators.name: ccaGlobalNumActiveAccelerators
ccaGlobalNumActiveAccelerators.description: The number of crypto accelerators which are in state 'active'.

ccaGlobalNumNonOperAccelerators.name: ccaGlobalNumNonOperAccelerators
ccaGlobalNumNonOperAccelerators.description: The number of crypto accelerators which are in a state other than 'active'.

ccaGlobalInOctets.name: ccaGlobalInOctets
ccaGlobalInOctets.description: The total number of octets input to all the crypto accelerators installed in the device. The value is cumulative from last reboot of the managed entity.

ccaGlobalOutOctets.name: ccaGlobalOutOctets
ccaGlobalOutOctets.description: The total number of octets output by all the crypto accelerators installed in the device. The value is cumulative from last reboot of the managed entity.

ccaGlobalInPkts.name: ccaGlobalInPkts
ccaGlobalInPkts.description: The total number of packets input to all the crypto accelerators installed in the device. The value is cumulative from last reboot of the managed entity.

ccaGlobalOutPkts.name: ccaGlobalOutPkts
ccaGlobalOutPkts.description: The total number of packets output by all the crypto accelerators installed in the device. The value is cumulative from last reboot of the managed entity.

ccaGlobalOutErrPkts.name: ccaGlobalOutErrPkts
ccaGlobalOutErrPkts.description: The total number of packets output by all the crypto accelerators installed in the device which were found to be generated with errors (checksum errors, other errors). The value is cumulative from last reboot of the managed entity.

ccaAcceleratorTable.name: ccaAcceleratorTable
ccaAcceleratorTable.description: The crypto accelerator table. There is one entry in this table for each crypto accelerator installed in the managed device.

ccaAcceleratorEntry.name: ccaAcceleratorEntry
ccaAcceleratorEntry.description: Each entry contains the attributes and statistics of a crypto accelerator module installed on the managed device.

ccaAcclIndex.name: ccaAcclIndex
ccaAcclIndex.description: The index uniquely identifying a specific crypto accelerator.

ccaAcclEntPhysicalIndex.name: ccaAcclEntPhysicalIndex
ccaAcclEntPhysicalIndex.description: The value of entPhysicalIndex of the module corresponding to this conceptual row or zero, if the module is not an entity listed in 'entPhysicalTable' of rfc2737.

ccaAcclStatus.name: ccaAcclStatus
ccaAcclStatus.description: The state of the crypto accelerator corresponding to this row.

ccaAcclType.name: ccaAcclType
ccaAcclType.description: The type of the crypto accelerator corresponding to this row.

ccaAcclVersion.name: ccaAcclVersion
ccaAcclVersion.description: The version string of the firmware of the crypto accelerator corresponding to this row.

ccaAcclSlot.name: ccaAcclSlot
ccaAcclSlot.description: The slot number of the crypto accelerator corresponding to this row.

ccaAcclActiveTime.name: ccaAcclActiveTime
ccaAcclActiveTime.description: The number of seconds elapsed since the crypto accelerator corresponding to this row transitioned into the 'active' state.

ccaAcclInPkts.name: ccaAcclInPkts
ccaAcclInPkts.description: The number of packets input to this module for processing since the last reboot of the device.

ccaAcclOutPkts.name: ccaAcclOutPkts
ccaAcclOutPkts.description: The number of packets output by this module after processing, since last reboot of the device.

ccaAcclOutBadPkts.name: ccaAcclOutBadPkts
ccaAcclOutBadPkts.description: The number of packets output by this module after processing which had crypto errors, since last reboot of the device.

ccaAcclInOctets.name: ccaAcclInOctets
ccaAcclInOctets.description: The number of octets input to this module for processing since last reboot of the device.

ccaAcclOutOctets.name: ccaAcclOutOctets
ccaAcclOutOctets.description: The number of octets output by this module after processing since last reboot of the device.

ccaAcclHashOutboundPkts.name: ccaAcclHashOutboundPkts
ccaAcclHashOutboundPkts.description: The number of packets output by this module which were prepared for hash validation since the last reboot of the device. Hash validation is a cryptographic operation used to verify the integrity of a block of data received from a trusted source.

ccaAcclHashOutboundOctets.name: ccaAcclHashOutboundOctets
ccaAcclHashOutboundOctets.description: The number of octets output by this module which were prepared for hash validation since the last reboot of the device.

ccaAcclHashInboundPkts.name: ccaAcclHashInboundPkts
ccaAcclHashInboundPkts.description: The number of packets input to this module which required hash validation since the last reboot of the device.

ccaAcclHashInboundOctets.name: ccaAcclHashInboundOctets
ccaAcclHashInboundOctets.description: The number of octets input to this module which were authenticated using hash validation since the last reboot of the device.

ccaAcclEncryptPkts.name: ccaAcclEncryptPkts
ccaAcclEncryptPkts.description: The number of packets input to this module which required encryption since the last reboot of the device.

ccaAcclEncryptOctets.name: ccaAcclEncryptOctets
ccaAcclEncryptOctets.description: The number of octets input to this module which required encryption since the last reboot of the device.

ccaAcclDecryptPkts.name: ccaAcclDecryptPkts
ccaAcclDecryptPkts.description: The number of packets input to this module which required decryption since the last reboot of the device.

ccaAcclDecryptOctets.name: ccaAcclDecryptOctets
ccaAcclDecryptOctets.description: The number of octets input to this module which required decryption since the last reboot of the device.

ccaAcclTransformsTotal.name: ccaAcclTransformsTotal
ccaAcclTransformsTotal.description: The number of cryptographic transformations performed by this crypto accelerator since the last reboot of the device.

ccaAcclDropsPkts.name: ccaAcclDropsPkts
ccaAcclDropsPkts.description: The number of packets input to this module which were dropped prior to processing since the last reboot of the device.

ccaAcclRandRequests.name: ccaAcclRandRequests
ccaAcclRandRequests.description: The number of requests received by this crypto accelerator to generate random numbers since the last reboot of the device.

ccaAcclRandReqFails.name: ccaAcclRandReqFails
ccaAcclRandReqFails.description: The number of random number requests received by this module which were not fulfilled, counted since the last reboot of the device.

ccaAcclDHKeysGenerated.name: ccaAcclDHKeysGenerated
ccaAcclDHKeysGenerated.description: The number of Diffie Hellman key pairs generated by this module since the last reboot.

ccaAcclDHDerivedSecretKeys.name: ccaAcclDHDerivedSecretKeys
ccaAcclDHDerivedSecretKeys.description: The number of times this module has derived Diffie Hellman secret keys since the last reboot of the device.

ccaAcclRSAKeysGenerated.name: ccaAcclRSAKeysGenerated
ccaAcclRSAKeysGenerated.description: The number of times a new RSA key pair was generated by this module, counted since the last time this module assumed 'active' status.

ccaAcclRSASignings.name: ccaAcclRSASignings
ccaAcclRSASignings.description: The number of times an RSA Digital Signature has been generated by this module, counted since the last time this module assumed 'active' status.

ccaAcclRSAVerifications.name: ccaAcclRSAVerifications
ccaAcclRSAVerifications.description: The number of times an RSA Digital Signature has been verified by this module, counted since the last time this module assumed 'active' status.

ccaAcclRSAEncryptPkts.name: ccaAcclRSAEncryptPkts
ccaAcclRSAEncryptPkts.description: The number of packets input to this module which required RSA encryption, counted since the last time this module assumed 'active' status.

ccaAcclRSAEncryptOctets.name: ccaAcclRSAEncryptOctets
ccaAcclRSAEncryptOctets.description: The number of octets input to this module which required RSA encryption, counted since the last time this module assumed 'active' status.

ccaAcclRSADecryptPkts.name: ccaAcclRSADecryptPkts
ccaAcclRSADecryptPkts.description: The number of packets input to this module which required RSA decryption, counted since the last time this module assumed 'active' status.

ccaAcclRSADecryptOctets.name: ccaAcclRSADecryptOctets
ccaAcclRSADecryptOctets.description: The number of octets input to this module which required RSA decryption, counted since the last time this module assumed 'active' status.

ccaAcclDSAKeysGenerated.name: ccaAcclDSAKeysGenerated
ccaAcclDSAKeysGenerated.description: The number of times DSA key pair has been generated by this module, counted since the last time this module assumed 'active' status.

ccaAcclDSASignings.name: ccaAcclDSASignings
ccaAcclDSASignings.description: The number of times DSA signature has been generated by this module, counted since the last time this module assumed 'active' status.

ccaAcclDSAVerifications.name: ccaAcclDSAVerifications
ccaAcclDSAVerifications.description: The number of times DSA signature has been verified by this module, counted since the last time this module assumed 'active' status.

ccaAcclOutboundSSLRecords.name: ccaAcclOutboundSSLRecords
ccaAcclOutboundSSLRecords.description: The number of combined outbound hash/encrypt SSL records processed by this module, counted since the last time this module assumed 'active' status.

ccaAcclInboundSSLRecords.name: ccaAcclInboundSSLRecords
ccaAcclInboundSSLRecords.description: The number of combined inbound hash/encrypt SSL records processed by this module, counted since the last time this module assumed 'active' status.

ccaProtocolStatsTable.name: ccaProtocolStatsTable
ccaProtocolStatsTable.description: The crypto accelerator statistics catalogued by security protocol causing the activity. There is only entry in this table for each security protocol listed in the textual convention 'CAProtocolType'.

ccaProtocolStatsEntry.name: ccaProtocolStatsEntry
ccaProtocolStatsEntry.description: Each entry contains the statistics corresponding to a specific security protocol.

ccaProtId.name: ccaProtId
ccaProtId.description: The index uniquely identifies the security protocol for which this row summarizes the statistics.

ccaProtPktEncryptsReqs.name: ccaProtPktEncryptsReqs
ccaProtPktEncryptsReqs.description: The number of payload encrypt requests received by the crypto accelerators from this security protocol, counted since the last reboot of the device.

ccaProtPktDecryptsReqs.name: ccaProtPktDecryptsReqs
ccaProtPktDecryptsReqs.description: The number of payload decrypt requests received by the crypto accelerators from this security protocol, counted since the last reboot of the device.

ccaProtHmacCalcReqs.name: ccaProtHmacCalcReqs
ccaProtHmacCalcReqs.description: The number of times keyed HMAC calculation requests were received by the crypto accelerators due to the operation of this security protocol, counted since the last reboot of the device.

ccaProtSaCreateReqs.name: ccaProtSaCreateReqs
ccaProtSaCreateReqs.description: The number of times requests for creation of security associations were received by the crypto accelerators from this security protocol, counted since the last reboot of the device.

ccaProtSaRekeyReqs.name: ccaProtSaRekeyReqs
ccaProtSaRekeyReqs.description: The number of times requests for rekeying of existing security associations were received by the crypto accelerators from this security protocol, counted since the last reboot of the device.

ccaProtSaDeleteReqs.name: ccaProtSaDeleteReqs
ccaProtSaDeleteReqs.description: The number of times requests for deletion of security associations were received by the crypto accelerators from this security protocol, counted since the last reboot of the device.

ccaProtPktEncapReqs.name: ccaProtPktEncapReqs
ccaProtPktEncapReqs.description: The number of times requests for payload encapsulation were received by the crypto accelerators from this security protocol, counted since the last reboot of the device.

ccaProtPktDecapReqs.name: ccaProtPktDecapReqs
ccaProtPktDecapReqs.description: The number of times requests for payload decapsulation were received by the crypto accelerators from this security protocol, counted since the last reboot of the device.

ccaProtNextPhaseKeyAllocReqs.name: ccaProtNextPhaseKeyAllocReqs
ccaProtNextPhaseKeyAllocReqs.description: The number of times requests for allocation of keys for the next phase of the protocol operation which were received by the crypto accelerators from this security protocol, counted since the last reboot of the device. As an example, for IKE, this would identify the number of times key allocation requests for Quick Mode were received by the crypto accelerator from the IKE protocol engine.

ccaProtRndGenReqs.name: ccaProtRndGenReqs
ccaProtRndGenReqs.description: The number of times requests for generation of random number(s) were received by the crypto accelerators from this security protocol, counted since the last reboot of the device.

ccaProtFailedReqs.name: ccaProtFailedReqs
ccaProtFailedReqs.description: The number of times requests received from this security protocol could not be fulfilled, counted since the last reboot of the device.

ccaNotifCntlAcclInserted.name: ccaNotifCntlAcclInserted
ccaNotifCntlAcclInserted.description: This variable controls the generation of 'ciscoCryAccelInserted' notification. When this variable is set to 'true', generation of the notification is enabled. When this variable is set to 'false', generation of the notification is disabled.

ccaNotifCntlAcclRemoved.name: ccaNotifCntlAcclRemoved
ccaNotifCntlAcclRemoved.description: This variable controls the generation of 'ciscoCryAccelRemoved' notification. When this variable is set to 'true', generation of the notification is enabled. When this variable is set to 'false', generation of the notification is disabled.

ccaNotifCntlAcclOperational.name: ccaNotifCntlAcclOperational
ccaNotifCntlAcclOperational.description: This variable controls the generation of 'ciscoCryAccelOperational' notification. When this variable is set to 'true', generation of the notification is enabled. When this variable is set to 'false', generation of the notification is disabled.

ccaNotifCntlAcclDisabled.name: ccaNotifCntlAcclDisabled
ccaNotifCntlAcclDisabled.description: This variable controls the generation of 'ciscoCryAccelDisabled' notification. When this variable is set to 'true', generation of the notification is enabled. When this variable is set to 'false', generation of the notification is disabled.

ciscoCryAccelInserted.name: ciscoCryAccelInserted
ciscoCryAccelInserted.description: A crypto accelerator module has been inserted into the managed device.

ciscoCryAccelRemoved.name: ciscoCryAccelRemoved
ciscoCryAccelRemoved.description: A crypto accelerator module has been removed from the managed device.

ciscoCryAccelOperational.name: ciscoCryAccelOperational
ciscoCryAccelOperational.description: A crypto accelerator module has become operational.

ciscoCryAccelDisabled.name: ciscoCryAccelDisabled
ciscoCryAccelDisabled.description: A crypto accelerator module has become non-operational.

ciscoCryAccelMIBCompliance.name: ciscoCryAccelMIBCompliance
ciscoCryAccelMIBCompliance.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement the CISCO Crypto Accelerator MIB.

ciscoCryAccCapacityGroup.name: ciscoCryAccCapacityGroup
ciscoCryAccCapacityGroup.description: This group consists of all the MIB variables defined under crAcCapacity using which the management station may determine the limits of capacity of the managed device with regards to the support of crypto accelerators.

ciscoCryAccSummaryActivityGroup.name: ciscoCryAccSummaryActivityGroup
ciscoCryAccSummaryActivityGroup.description: This group consists of the counters which model the summary activity of the crypto accelerators in the managed entity.

ciscoCryAccModuleActivityGroup.name: ciscoCryAccModuleActivityGroup
ciscoCryAccModuleActivityGroup.description: This group consists of the counters which model the summary activity of the crypto accelerators in the managed entity. Following are definitions of some terms used in this compliance group: Crypto Accelerator 'Crypto Accelerator' denotes a hardware or software device which the managed entity uses to offload some or all computations pertaining to cryptographic operations. A crypto accelerator module may be implemented as a Field Removable Unit or an integrated hardware element such an Application Specific Integrated Chip (ASIC). Module The term 'Module' has been used in this MIB to denote a hardware crypto accelerator. Diffie-Hellman The Diffie-Hellman key agreement protocol (also called exponential key agreement) was developed by Diffie and Hellman in 1976. The protocol allows two users to exchange a secret key over an insecure medium without any prior secrets. RSA An Internet encryption and authentication system that uses an algorithm developed in 1977 by Ron Rivest, Adi Shamir, and Leonard Adleman. DSS Digital Signature Standard (DSS) is the digital signature algorithm (DSA) developed by the U.S. National Security Agency (NSA) to generate a digital signature for the authentication of electronic documents. IPsec IP security protocol. SSL Secure Socket Layer Protocol. SSH Secure Shell Protocol. PKI Public Key Infrastructure

ciscoCryAccProtocolActivityGroup.name: ciscoCryAccProtocolActivityGroup
ciscoCryAccProtocolActivityGroup.description: This group consists of the counters which model the protocol-specific activity of the crypto accelerators in the managed entity.

ciscoCryAccNotifsCntlGroup.name: ciscoCryAccNotifsCntlGroup
ciscoCryAccNotifsCntlGroup.description: This group consists of all the MIB variables which allow the network management station to control the emission of the notifications defined in this MIB. Per a different compliance clause dfined in this module, the agent is not required to provide write access to these MIB variables.

ciscoCryAccNotifsGroup.name: ciscoCryAccNotifsGroup
ciscoCryAccNotifsGroup.description: This group consists of all the notifications defined to signal the change in status and operation of crypto accelerator modules.
